SIMPLE: hamstring
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hamstring
<hw>Ham"string`</hw> <pr>(h⟦acr⟧m"str⟦icr⟧ng`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>One of the great tendons situated in each side
of the ham, or space back of the knee, and connected with the muscles of
the back of the thigh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hamstring</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hamstring
<hw>Ham"string`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Hamstrung</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Hamstringing</conjf>. See <er>String</er>.]</vmorph> <def>To lame
or disable by cutting the tendons of the ham or knee; to hough; hence,
to cripple; to incapacitate; to disable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So have they <qex>hamstrung</qex> the valor of the subject by
seeking to effeminate us all at home.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hamular</ent>⟦br⟧
